This Friday marks the unofficial start of the festive season shopping and South Africans are taking full advantage of the specials. Known as Black Friday, it is tradition for the fourth Friday of November to be a day of shopping madness. The tradition has caught on in South Africa as thousands of shoppers flock to malls, shops and online retailers to take advantage of the special savings. South Africans did not miss an opportunity to have fun as #BlackFriday jokes took over Social media.